HEADWORD: Taguan
<hw>Tag"u*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From the native name
in the East Indies.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A large flying
squirrel (<spn>Pteromys petuarista</spn>). Its body becomes two feet
long, with a large bushy tail nearly as long.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

